        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A muscular channelopathy presenting with a pure myotonia dramatically aggravated by potassium ingestion with variable cold sensitivity and no episodic weakness. This group includes three forms: myotonia fluctuans myotonia permanens and acetazolamide-responsive myotonia."
        },
